Delete mdp_dist. All future updates should be made in release-manager branch.

From now on mdp_dist will only exist in the release-manager branch.
If the release manager decides to update, the specific commit of the master branch
should be merged to the release-manager branch. (Of course, care has to be taken
that the mdp_dist folder is not removed from release-manager after merging.)

Revert "Delete mdp_dist. All future updates should be made in release-manager branch."

This reverts commit ba2743e19d6edd5df46427c3abf1304d7f259b76.
The idea of a release-manager branch doesn't actually pay off, because
all the files in mdp_dist should actually be in remote master branch
apart from the two scripts (gendist & cleandist). I think the two
scripts can live in the master branch: this would even help the wannabe
mdp-forker ;-)

Moved release files in root of master branch.
